The paper deals with the problem of detecting and quantifying information leaks through timing side channels, which is a common concern in computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves using neural networks to learn the timing behavior of programs and analyze them to quantify information leaks, which involves techniques from software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed approach, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques that are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
